FRONTMATTER
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Required fields — always present:
  title   Human-readable name. Example: "Sprint Retrospective"
  type    One of: planning | implementation | post-implementation
          | documentation | skill | content
  tags    2–3 tags from TAGS.md. Syntax: [tag1, tag2, tag3]

Optional fields — skill and routing templates only:
  description    One sentence: what this skill does and for whom.
  use_when       One sentence: the precise trigger condition.
  output_type    One of: strategy | copy | audit | structure |
                 analysis | recommendation
  related_skills Array of filenames without extension.

Do not add fields outside this list.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
INSTRUCTION BLOCK
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Every template has one HTML comment block immediately after
frontmatter. Opening line must be: INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE MODEL:

Six rules required in every instruction block:
  1. Your output must be this document with every section filled in.
  2. Do not write prose, summaries, or commentary outside the structure.
  3. Replace every {{PLACEHOLDER}} with the appropriate content.
  4. Remove all HTML comments (including this block) from the output.
  5. Do not add, remove, or reorder sections.
  6. Do not leave any section empty or containing placeholder text.

Add template-specific rules after the six common rules.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PLACEHOLDERS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Syntax: {{UPPERCASE_SNAKE_CASE}}

Standard placeholders:
  {{PROJECT_NAME}}  Name of the project
  {{DATE}}          ISO date (YYYY-MM-DD)
  {{AUTHOR}}        Author name or handle
  {{PROMPT}}        The user's input — always rendered as a blockquote

{{PROMPT}} must appear as a blockquote in the first content
section: > {{PROMPT}}

Name custom placeholders after the concept they represent.
  Good: {{API_ENDPOINT}}, {{DECISION_TITLE}}, {{ERROR_TYPE}}
  Bad:  {{THING}}, {{ITEM}}, {{VALUE}}

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION STRUCTURE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

H2 (##) for top-level sections. H3 (###) for subsections.
Avoid H4+ unless embedding a detailed reference guide.

Tables: always include a header separator row (|---|---|).
If a downstream script parses the table, add this rule to the
instruction block: "Column order must be preserved."

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[BOT] / [HUMAN] TAGS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Use in list items only — never in headings or prose.
  - <description> [BOT]    implementable by an AI agent
  - <description> [HUMAN]  requires human judgment or action

A [HUMAN] item is a mandatory checkpoint. Dependent [BOT] items
may not proceed until it is resolved. Use sparingly.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPTIONAL SECTIONS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Default: every section is required — never omit.

To allow omission, say so explicitly in the instruction block:
  "If <condition>, omit this section entirely."
  OR
  "If <condition>, write N/A."
Use one strategy consistently within a template.

